-MwSIQBB5w1Qu09s_8C-.text: Police are responding to an unconfirmed report of shots fired in the area.

-MwSInNGxnJYCAxHZLXP.text: An additional report states a person has been shot. It is unclear where the shooter is.

-MwSK0QcgnWfjdxdki2z.text: Police on the scene have located two people shot and have requested medics.

-MwSLTckk11oEEj3aBbZ.text: Medical personnel have advised they are transporting the victims to a area hospital.

-MwSMLUWic4SAJmnhqhs.text: Police have located two other people who have been shot at a local hospital, bringing the total number of people with gunshot wounds to four.

-MwSjUs3hH4yZdZhsfZt.text: According to a tweet from Saint Paul PD, one person was fatally wounded after four people were shot at a funeral for Cassanova Carter at 11:20 this morning on the West Side of Saint Paul.

-MwSqjwrxpv2Gw5DXdjj.text: Officers state several other people sustained minor injuries after disorder caused by the gunfire outside Bradshaw Funeral and Cremation Services.

-MwT-1ouNvAoy-NBtSc5.text: Police have found evidence of gunfire that struck a nearby building and are investigating at the scene.

nib.text:
One man was killed and three others victims were injured—one of them critically—in a shooting outside a funeral home in St. Paul's West Side late Monday morning, police confirmed in an updated statement Monday afternoon.

The shooting happened at about 11:20 a.m. outside a funeral home in the 400 block of Humboldt Avenue, police said.

Funeral services were being held for 26-year-old Casanova Carter, who was fatally shot February 1 in the 700 block of Winslow Avenue on the West Side.

First responders at the scene Monday morning found a 28-year-old man with fatal injuries, along with a man in his 30s with a gunshot wound to the neck, a person in their 20s with a gunshot wound to the abdomen back, and femur, and a man in his 20s who was grazed in the face.

According to radio transmissions, several others may have sustained minor injuries in the chaos after the shooting.

Police rendered first aid. Medics took the shooting victims to the hospital. The 28-year-old man was pronounced deceased. The man with injuries to the abdomen, back, and femur was in critical condition. The other two were treated but their exact condition was not disclosed.

Police remained on scene to gather forensic evidence.

As of Monday afternoon, police said they had not made any arrests, but the shooting did not appear random.

Anyone with information about Monday's or the Feb. 1 shooting of Carter is urged by police to call them at [651-266-5650](tel:651-266-5650).
